that, what do you do?

01:01:39.210 --> 01:01:41.100
Take a picture.

01:01:41.100 --> 01:01:41.600
I did.

01:01:41.600 --> 01:01:42.610
I took a picture.

01:01:45.205 --> 01:01:47.080
DANA HAN-KLEIN: You
gotta keep hip, you know.

01:01:47.080 --> 01:01:48.538
BILL NYE: Yeah,
well, I do my best.

01:01:48.538 --> 01:01:50.380
I do my best.

01:01:50.380 --> 01:01:52.750
DANA HAN-KLEIN: But I think
that people like yourself,

01:01:52.750 --> 01:01:54.610
we're grateful for you
coming to places like Google.

01:01:54.610 --> 01:01:55.820
BILL NYE: Well, thank
you for inviting me.

01:01:55.820 --> 01:01:56.670
I love you guys.

01:01:56.670 --> 01:01:58.532
It's so great.

01:01:58.532 --> 01:02:00.740
DANA HAN-KLEIN: Speaking
about the joys of education,

01:02:00.740 --> 01:02:02.720
so I have two final questions.

01:02:02.720 --> 01:02:03.970
BILL NYE: Two final questions.

01:02:03.970 --> 01:02:06.180
DANA HAN-KLEIN: You talk
about how we all have

01:02:06.180 --> 01:02:07.725
30,000 or so days on earth.

01:02:07.725 --> 01:02:08.350
BILL NYE: Yeah.

01:02:08.350 --> 01:02:08.950
Oh, man.

01:02:08.950 --> 01:02:09.700
You read the book.

01:02:09.700 --> 01:02:11.890
DANA HAN-KLEIN: I read the book.

01:02:11.890 --> 01:02:15.010
What do you want your
legacy from that to be?

01:02:15.010 --> 01:02:17.825
Do you want it to be
combating climate change, or--

01:02:17.825 --> 01:02:18.450
BILL NYE: Yeah.

01:02:18.450 --> 01:02:19.410
DANA HAN-KLEIN: OK.

01:02:19.410 --> 01:02:19.910
All right.

01:02:19.910 --> 01:02:20.980
Answered.

01:02:20.980 --> 01:02:24.450
BILL NYE: I want you guys
to cure cancer, I mean,

01:02:24.450 --> 01:02:26.160
