01:02:39.550 --> 01:02:41.940
And the way to do that
is through education

01:02:41.940 --> 01:02:46.890
so that the human population
naturally starts to go down.

01:02:46.890 --> 01:02:49.800
And you guys, I mean,
this is so sweet.

01:02:49.800 --> 01:02:52.880
Anyway, we're all playing
the hand we're dealt, right?

01:02:52.880 --> 01:02:56.420
So I was born at a
time, in the 1950s,

01:02:56.420 --> 01:03:00.160
and one of the things
that's very troubling when

01:03:00.160 --> 01:03:02.460
you get to be my
age is you realize

01:03:02.460 --> 01:03:04.730
that you're going to die.

01:03:04.730 --> 01:03:08.790
I went through many
years pretty sure

01:03:08.790 --> 01:03:13.610
that everybody else was getting
older and was going to die,

01:03:13.610 --> 01:03:16.770
but I was fine.

01:03:16.770 --> 01:03:20.540
But is anybody familiar
with the game of rugby?

01:03:20.540 --> 01:03:22.320
Rugby football?

01:03:22.320 --> 01:03:25.950
Yeah, so unlike US
football-- which we can all

01:03:25.950 --> 01:03:28.440
have a whole nother discussion
about whatever they're

01:03:28.440 --> 01:03:34.420
doing-- but can't throw
the ball forward in rugby.

01:03:34.420 --> 01:03:39.900
So I often think of
this metaphor as,

01:03:39.900 --> 01:03:41.520
what you do is you
run with the ball.

01:03:41.520 --> 01:03:45.550
You try to get as many defenders
to come after you as possible,

01:03:45.550 --> 01:03:47.770
and then throw it to
the next guy in the line

01:03:47.770 --> 01:03:51.600
so that he's got an open field
and can advance the ball.

01:03:51.600 --> 01:03:54.850
So I'm doing my best
to throw the ball

01:03:54.850 --> 01:03:59.480
of scientific discovery and
understanding to you guys

01:03:59.480 --> 01:04:03.410
so that you can advance
it down the field of life.

01:04:03.410 --> 01:04:05.550
Wow, man.

